@threevincenzo Proof of what? I’m not sure what the solution is. Change doesn’t come overnight. Just pointing out the nuance of the discussion between fair and fact. Need to approach it from both angles. Was never arguing with your first point, but adding my thoughts on how to move forward.

@threevincenzo Which is why we should work to find another solution… I agree that what we’re currently doing isn’t fair to everyone. Sooooo we should find a solution that can still be inclusive and understanding of everyone. Doesn’t need to be one or the other. It can be both.

@threevincenzo Being inclusive to some =/= being exclusive to rest. Just because the current solution doesn’t work or isn’t the fairest doesn’t mean we shouldn’t work to find a way to be inclusive of everyone.

@threevincenzo There’s some delusional people that try to argue that but I think the integral part of the discussion is understanding that is true and then finding ways to still be accepting, inclusive and fair to all people. Tough situation to navigate in sports especially.
